******
[1] Montana (Cascade County)
Date: Thu 11 Dec 2014
Source: KRTV [edited]
http://www.krtv.com/news/3rd-case-of-pertussis-confirmed-at-cmr-in-great-falls/


The City-County Health Department in Great Falls [Cascade County, Montana] says there are now 3 confirmed cases of pertussis, often called whooping cough, among students at C.M. Russell High School [CMR].

Since 1 Jan 2014, there have been 423 cases of pertussis in Montana, with 16 of those cases in Cascade County. The Great Falls Public School District announced on Thursday, 11 Dec 2014, that 2 people at CMR had been diagnosed.

CCHD health officer Tanya Houston said that they are conducting "contact-tracing" in an attempt to find anyone who has come into contact with people that have been diagnosed. If these people have symptoms they will recommend that they contact their healthcare provider for testing and treatment. Contact-tracing is how they discovered the 3rd case of whooping cough at CMR.

[Byline: Margaret DeMarco]

