******
[2] Pennsylvania (Allegheny County)
Date: Thu 11 Dec 2014
Source: WTAE [edited]
http://www.wtae.com/health/allegheny-county-health-department-reports-growing-incidence-of-pertussis/30177816


The Allegheny County [Pennsylvania] Health Department today [11 Dec 2014] announced that a growing number of pertussis cases are being reported in the county. "To prevent further transmission of the disease, we would like to remind residents of all ages, but especially school-age children, to follow proper cough etiquette and hand washing techniques. This includes coughing or sneezing into a tissue or sleeve and washing hands frequently with soap and water for 20 seconds," said Health Director Dr. Karen Hacker.

