******
[3] New York (Clinton County)
Date: Wed 3 Dec 2014
Source: Press Republican [edited]
http://www.pressrepublican.com/news/local_news/pertussis-confirmed-in-clinton-county-schools/article_b06299d8-148d-5200-9bd1-cfadcff10f47.html


The Clinton County [New York State] Health Department has confirmed that multiple area schools have recently been affected by pertussis. On Tuesday, 2 Dec 2014, the Plattsburgh City School District sent a letter informing parents that a small number of cases of the highly contagious disease had been confirmed in more than one district building. The district wished to make people aware of the potential for exposure in an effort to break the cycle of transmission, according to Health Department public-health nurse Karen Merrill.

"Pertussis is also known as whooping cough, and that's because of the signature sound that is often heard when a person is coughing," Merrill said. "It's also known as the 100-day cough. And that's a long time to cough."

[Byline: Ashleigh Livingston]

